Reading books is my favourite way to level up. A good book is the closest thing we have to uploading information straight into our brain. It makes sense why - authors compress years of research and thinking into a book which takes you only a few hours to read.

I try to read as much as possible - averaging at least one book each week. It's had a strange effect on how I think: When I encounter problems I find myself flipping through a mental library of books. I can't always remember the exact solutions but I at least know where to go look for answers.

A lot of people at [OfferZen](https://www.offerzen.com/) have started reading startup books and I often find myself giving them recommendations. So recently I decided to review all the startup books I've ever read and compile a list of my favourite ones. I ended up with this list of 21 books!

